This repository is multi-licensed. There is no single license that covers
every file. To find the license that applies to a given file:

  1. If the file is inside one of the directories listed below, that
     directory's license applies.
  2. Otherwise, MIT applies (see LICENSE-MIT).

DIRECTORY                      LICENSE        FILE(S)
-----------------------------  -------------  --------------------------
third_party/mesen/             GPL-3.0        third_party/mesen/LICENSE
reference/build-mesen.sh,      GPL-3.0        LICENSE-GPL3
  reference/mesen_step.cpp,
  reference/mesen.wasm
corpus/roms/                   Per-ROM        corpus/README.md, LEGAL.md §2
spec/                          MIT            LICENSE-MIT
corpus/   (non-ROM files)      MIT            LICENSE-MIT
candidates/                    MIT            LICENSE-MIT
harness/                       MIT            LICENSE-MIT
quickstart/                    MIT            LICENSE-MIT
(repo root, configs, docs)     MIT            LICENSE-MIT

COMPILED ARTIFACTS

  reference/mesen.wasm     GPL-3.0 (compiled from Mesen2)
  harness/grader (binary)  MIT (loads reference wasm at arm's length;
                                see LEGAL.md §6.1)

BIOS AND ROMS

  gba_bios_stub.bin and spec/gba_bios_stub.bin are MIT-licensed original
  work. They are a clean-room reimplementation of a handful of GBA SWI
  entry points, not a copy of Nintendo's BIOS. See LEGAL.md §1.

  No commercial ROMs are included in this repository. ROMs under
  corpus/roms/ are homebrew or hardware test ROMs distributed under
  their own upstream licenses. See LEGAL.md §2.

For the plain-English explanation of how these licenses interact, what
our distribution obligations are, and why the BIOS stub and ROM corpus
are safe to ship, read LEGAL.md at the root of this repository.

The full text of each license is in:
  LICENSE-MIT                          (MIT license + scope notice)
  LICENSE-GPL3                         (GNU GPL v3.0)
  third_party/mesen/LICENSE            (Mesen2's GPL-3.0 copy)

